    "what_description": "Primula sulphurea is a species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae. It is a perennial herb with a rosette of basal leaves that are ovate to lanceolate in shape and have a crenate margin. The leaves are 10-20 cm long and 2-4 cm wide, with a glabrous surface and a petiole that is 1-2 cm long. The inflorescence is a corymb of 5-10 flowers that are bell-shaped and have a yellowish-orange color with a red or purple tint, and are 2-3 cm long and 1-2 cm wide. The flowers are borne in June and July and are fragrant, with 5 petals and 5 stamens.",
