    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Primula sulphurea are respiratory issues, such as bronchitis, due to its expectorant properties that help to loosen and clear mucus from the lungs. Inflammation, including swollen joints and skin irritations, can be reduced by applying Primula sulphurea's poultices or infusions, which contain salicylic acid, a known anti-inflammatory compound. Primula sulphurea's antiseptic properties also make it an effective treatment for wound infections, preventing the growth of pathogenic bacteria and promoting healing. Its antibacterial and antifungal properties also combat skin conditions like acne and eczema by reducing bacterial and fungal activity on the skin. Primula sulphurea's expectorant properties also alleviate coughs associated with tuberculosis.",
