    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Primula sulphurea are antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antiseptic. The antiseptic properties of this plant are attributed to the presence of volatile oils and flavonoids, which inhibit the growth of microorganisms and reduce the risk of infection. The anti-inflammatory properties of Primula sulphurea are due to the presence of saponins, which reduce inflammation and alleviate pain. The antioxidant properties of this plant are attributed to the presence of phenolic acids, which neutralize free radicals and prevent oxidative damage. The antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties of Primula sulphurea make it a potential treatment for wound healing and skin infections.",
