    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Primula sulphurea are iridoid glycosides, specifically primulaverin and primuline, which possess anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. These iridoids have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and enzymes, thereby reducing inflammation and tissue damage. The plant also contains phenolic acids, including caffeic acid and ferulic acid, which exhibit antioxidant activity, neutralizing free radicals and protecting cells from oxidative stress. Primula sulphurea's flavonoid content, including quercetin and kaempferol, contributes to its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects. The combination of these bioactive compounds in Primula sulphurea makes it a valuable source of natural remedies for wound healing and tissue repair.",
